All Implemented Interfaces:
Action, ActionListener, Cloneable, EventListener, Serializable
public abstract class ContextMenuAction
extends Action

defines an Action class that a ContextMenuProvider should use to populate a JMenu. By using ContextMenuAction, the currently identified Content will be made known to each ContextMenuAction.

Method Detail

setContent

protected void setContent(Content content)
this method is invoked after the containing JMenu has been constructed and chosen for use as a context menu. After this method is invoked, the getContent method can be used. Subclasses might want to over-ride this method in order to set whether or not the ContextMenuAction is enabled. If this is done, it is important to remember to invoke super.setContent(content)

Parameters:
content - the Content to be operated on

getContent

protected Content getContent()
provides the Content that this action will operate on. This method should only be used after the context menu has been created - a typical use would be within the actionPerformed method

Returns:
the Content to be operated on
